  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8ba18922ef01d4d4c8990ab10d716134, type: 3}
  m_Name: Slide13
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  questionText: From the above incident, explain why the test tube should not be
    heated at the bottom?
  referenceImage: {fileID: 0}
  explanationText: Heating the bottom of the test tube can cause the liquid to heat
    up too rapidly in that area, and the gas bubbles evolved push the liquid out.
    This is termed as bumping.
  options:
  - It causes uneven heating
  - Bubbles formed in the test tube may violently spurt out
  - Accidents can be caused with such heating
  - All of the above
  correctOptionIndex: 3
  correctDropId: 
  correctValue: 0
  tolerance: 0.1
